tissueExpression.summary: Cytoplasmic and nuclear expression in gastrointestinal tract, liver, pancreas and kidney. Detected at Medium expression levels in 13 of 78 analyzed normal tissue cell types.

subcellularLocation.summary: Localized to the nucleus but excluded from the nucleoli.

tissueExpression.summary: Gastrointestinal tract, hepatocytes, pancreas, adrenal, renal tubules, myoepithelial cells of breast and cardiac myocytes showed moderate cytoplasmic and nuclear positivity. Remaining normal tissues were negative.
Carcinoids, hepatocellular carcinomas and a few renal cancers exhibited moderate cytoplasmic and nuclear positivity. Remaining cancers were negative.

tissueExpression.summary: Moderate cytoplasmic and/or nuclear positivity was displayed in gastrointestinal glands, respiratory epithelia, hepatocytes, pancreas, heart myocytes and gall bladder. Small intestine was strongly stained. Remaining normal tissues were generally negative.

Moderate to strong nuclear and/or cytoplasmic immunoreactivity was observed in most carcinoids along with few colorectal, pancreatic, renal and liver cancers. Remaining cancer tissues were generally negative.
